#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code sliding window + frequency array use karta hai minimum valid substring nikalne ke liye.

1. Pehle t ke sab characters ko hash array me store kar dete hain.
   Ye batata hai ki kis character ki kitni need hai.
2. Right pointer se window expand karte hain.
3. Agar current character abhi needed tha (hash > 0),
   to cnt increase kar dete hain.
4. Har baar current character ko include karke hash value decrease kar dete hain.
5. Jab cnt == m ho jaata hai,
   matlab current window me t ke saare characters aa gaye hain.
6. Ab left pointer se window ko shrink karte hain
   taaki minimum valid window mil sake.
7. Shrink karte waqt agar koi needed character remove ho jaaye,
   to cnt kam kar dete hain aur window invalid ho jaati hai.
8. Har valid stage par minLen aur start index update karte rehte hain.

Main idea:
Window ko pehle valid banao, phir usse chhota karte jao
jab tak valid rahe, taaki minimum substring mil sake.

Time Complexity: O(n + m)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public String minWindow(String s, String t) {

        int left = 0;
        int right = 0;
        int cnt = 0;
        int minLen = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        int sIndex = -1;
        int n = s.length();
        int m = t.length();
        int[] hash = new int[256];
        Arrays.fill(hash, 0);
        //Pre insert all the t string characters
        for(int i=0; i<m; i++){
            hash[t.charAt(i)]++;
        }
        while(right < n){
            //meaning pre inserted
            if(hash[s.charAt(right)] > 0) cnt++;
            hash[s.charAt(right)]--;

            //if cnt == m hogya to jab tk iski value equal rhegi tab tak hum choti window dhundte rhenge
            while(cnt == m){
                if((right - left + 1) < minLen){
                    minLen = (right - left + 1);
                    sIndex = left;
                }
                hash[s.charAt(left)]++;
                if(hash[s.charAt(left)] > 0) cnt--;
                left++;
            }
            right++;
        }
        return (sIndex == -1) ? "" : s.substring(sIndex, sIndex + minLen);
    }
}
